Lemon Poppy Seed Muffins
  --Sur la Table

2 c unbleached ap flour + 1 tbsp for dusting raspberries
1 tsp baking powder
1/4 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp fine sea salt
1 c sugar
2 tbsp lemon zest
2 tbsp poppy seeds
1 c 2% or whole-fat Greek yogurt
1 c vegetable oil + extra for greasing pan
2 large eggs
1 tsp vanilla bean paste

Preheat oven to 350F. Prepare 12 cup muffin tray with papers and set aside. To a medium bowl, add 2 c flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt; whisk together and set aside. To a separate medium bowl, add the sugar, zest, poppy seeds, yogurt, oil, eggs, and vanilla; whisk until smooth and well combined. Add the dry ingredients to the wet mixture; stir just until combined. Bake for 20-25 min or until cakes are firm to the touch but still very moist in the center. Cool on a wire rack.
